NFTMinted(address,uint256).details: This event will be emitted inside mintNft function.

params.owner: will be address who call the mintNft function.
params.tokenId: will be the token id which user will have minted.

params._name: will be the name of the token.
params._nftTokenUris: will be the token metadata ipfs hashes.
params._root: will be the root hash of the merkle tree.
params._symbol: will be the symbol of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._proof: will be the hex value of proof with the give caller address generated from the merkle tree.
params._tokenUriIndex: will be the index number of NFT Uri select by the user.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
